nodes.bodyText: Very minor nit, I think SSL_V2_HELLO reads a bit better than SSL_V2HELLO.
Looks like the ListRejectAttributeChecker could be used here instead.

         ResourceTransformationDescriptionBuilder builder = chainedBuilder.createBuilder(ELYTRON_12_0_0, ELYTRON_11_0_0);
-

+                .getAttributeBuilder()
+                .addRejectCheck(new RejectAttributeChecker.SimpleAcceptListAttributeChecker(new ModelNode(ElytronDescriptionConstants.SSL_V2HELLO)), ElytronDescriptionConstants.PROTOCOLS)

nodes.bodyText: It would also be good to add a test for the case where SSLv2Hello is only configured on the server side.
Looks like it would be good to add one more test case that makes use of the default protocols on the server side and the client side to ensure that SSLv2Hello isn't enabled by default.

It would also be good to either tweak testCommunication or create a new method that could be used instead in order to assert that serverSocket.getEnabledProtocols(), clientSocket.getEnabledProtocols(), serverSocket.getSession().getProtocol(), and clientSocket.getSession().getProtocol() return the expected values.
I've modified testCommunication to check the configured protocols.
This can be removed now since it's unused.

I think double check that the same additions made in tls-sun.xml are also made in tls-ibm.xml and tls-oracle13plus.xml.xml. Notice that in TlsTestCase#prepare, we can see that one of these three test files will be used depending on the JDK version. So for any resources that we're adding for new test cases, we need to make sure that we add the same ones to all three test files.
